	xmlns:ui="http://java.sun.com/jsf/facelets"
	xmlns:f="http://java.sun.com/jsf/core"
	xmlns:h="http://java.sun.com/jsf/html"
	xmlns:rich="http://richfaces.org/rich"
	xmlns:a4j="http://richfaces.org/a4j"
	xmlns:jsflot="http://www.jsflot.org/taglib/jsflot">
	
<rich:panel id="firsttutPage" style="width: 100%;">
	<f:facet name="header">JSFlot Y-Axis</f:facet>
	The Chart Y-Axis can be configured using 7 attributed to the jsflot:flotchart tag. <br />
	<b>showYaxisLabels</b><br />
	Determines whether or not the Y Axis displays label for the tick points. Defaults to "true", but can be 
	overridden to "false" if needed.  <br />
	<b>yaxisTitle</b><br />
	If this varible is set, it contains a String value representing the Y-Axis label. <br /> 
	<b>yaxisTitleRotation</b><br />
	The number of degrees that the title is rotated. <br /> 
	<b>yaxisLabelRotation</b><br />
	The number of degrees that the labels are rotated. <br />
	<b>numberOfYAxisTicks</b><br />
	JSFlot will calculate an appropriate number of Y-Axis ticks. However this number can be overridden using this 
	attribute. Keep in mind though, that JSFlot might alter your suggested number somewhat for rendering purposes. <br /> 
	<b>yaxisMinValue</b><br />
	JSFlot will calculate a sensible minimum value for the Y-Axis based on the data supplied to JSFlot. This number can be overridden, 
	but keep in mind that some datapoints might be outside your desired minimum value.  <br />
	<b>yaxisMaxValue</b><br />
	JSFlot will calculate a sensible maximum value for the Y-Axis based on the data supplied to JSFlot. This number can be overridden, 
	but keep in mind that some datapoints might be outside your desired maximum value. <br /> 	
</rich:panel>

</ui:composition>